# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# cpanm (cpanminus) is the **Perl module installer**
# by Tatsuhiko Miyagawa — the modern, fast,
# dependency-resolving alternative to CPAN.pm.  Used
# by virtually every Perl developer.  Pivots from Ruby
# OptionParser (R280 reek) into the **Perl language
# tooling cluster**.  Sister to cpan / cpanfile /
# perlbrew / plenv (Perl ecosystem tools).  **MAJOR
# MILESTONE**: corpus's **first documented Perl
# Getopt::Long CLI** — adds Perl to the cross-language
# CLI taxonomy (20 library variants now).
#
# Critical extraction note: cpanm uses **Perl's stdlib
# `Getopt::Long`** at `use Getopt::Long ()` — corpus's
# **first documented Perl Getopt::Long CLI**.
# `Getopt::Long` is **the** standard Perl CLI library
# — built into the Perl stdlib (no CPAN install
# needed).  Used by virtually every Perl CLI tool
# (cpanm, cpan, perlcritic, perltidy, etc.).  Extends
# the **cross-language CLI taxonomy** to TWENTY
# library variants (R279 added Dart; R280 added Ruby;
# R281 adds Perl): Rust (6), Go (4), Python (3),
# Crystal OptionParser (R269), Haskell optparse-
# applicative (R270), OCaml Cmdliner (R271), C POSIX
# getopt (R272), Java picocli (R276), Kotlin clikt
# (R277), Scala decline (R278), Dart args (R279), Ruby
# OptionParser (R280), **Perl Getopt::Long** (R281 —
# NEW).  **MAJOR PATTERN MILESTONE**: 20 cross-language
# CLI library variants documented.
#
# Critical extraction note: cpanm uses **Perl
# Getopt::Long's SUFFIX SYNTAX** at Compat.pm:157-229
# — Getopt::Long encodes option metadata via SUFFIX
# CHARACTERS in the option name string:
#   - `'f|force'`     — bare flag (`-f` or `--force`)
#                       turning on a boolean
#   - `'n|notest!'`   — `!` suffix = AUTO-NEGATABLE
#                       (auto-generates `--notest`
#                       AND `--no-notest`)
#   - `'l|local-lib=s'` — `=s` suffix = string value
#                         required
#   - `'configure-timeout=i'` — `=i` suffix = integer
#                               value required
#   - `'mirror=s@'`   — `=s@` suffix = string array
#                       (repeatable; collects into
#                       arrayref)
# Plus `|` separates short and long names (left =
# short, right = long).  Documents the **Perl
# Getopt::Long suffix-syntax-as-type-spec** pattern
# — distinct from clap derive's struct-field-type
# auto-detection (R260 dua), Click's `type=int` kwarg
# (R266 uvicorn), and Ruby OptionParser's inline-
# allowed-values-list (R280 reek).  Getopt::Long
# encodes ALL option metadata in the OPTION NAME
# STRING itself — most compressed CLI specification
# format in any language.  Corpus's **first documented
# suffix-syntax type spec**.
#
# Critical extraction note: cpanm uses
# **`Getopt::Long::Configure("bundling")`** at
# Compat.pm:155 — enables Getopt::Long's BUNDLING
# mode where short flags can be combined.  E.g.
# `-vqf` is equivalent to `-v -q -f`.  Without
# `bundling`, Getopt::Long would treat `-vqf` as a
# long option `-vqf` (which would fail).  Documents
# the **bundling-mode opt-in pattern** — corpus's
# first.  Distinct from POSIX getopt (R272 blink)
# which has bundling enabled by default and Go stdlib
# flag (R264 ctop) which doesn't support bundling at
# all.  Ruby OptionParser also doesn't have bundling.
# Plus other Getopt::Long Configure options include
# `no_ignore_case`, `pass_through`, `gnu_compat`,
# `require_order` — each enables/disables specific
# behaviors.  Corpus's **first documented Configure
# opt-in mode**.
#
# Critical extraction note: cpanm uses **`!`
# auto-negatable on many flags** at Compat.pm:158,
# 160, 163, 176, 177, 179, 186, 187, 189, 190, 192,
# 198-204, 211-214, 225 — total of ~20 auto-negatable
# flags via the `!` suffix.  Each automatically gets
# a `--no-FLAG` form.  Documents the **5th
# auto-negatable pattern** now in the corpus:
#   (a) Click slash-paired `--FLAG/--no-FLAG` (R266
#       uvicorn — explicit paired declaration)
#   (b) Rust clap explicit separate `--no-X` flag
#       (typical — manual second flag)
#   (c) Dart args auto-negatable OPT-OUT via
#       `negatable: false` (R279 gpth — opt-out from
#       auto-negatable default)
#   (d) Ruby OptionParser `'--[no-]flag'` explicit
#       syntax (R280 reek — explicit `[no-]` prefix
#       in name)
#   (e) **Perl Getopt::Long `!` suffix** (R281 cpanm
#       — single-char suffix in name)
# 5 enable/disable flag patterns NOW documented.
# Corpus's **first documented `!` suffix for
# auto-negatable**.
#
# Critical extraction note: cpanm reads **env var
# `PERL_CPANM_OPT` for extra ARGV entries** at
# Compat.pm:152 — `push @ARGV, grep length, split /
# \s+/, $self->env('OPT')` splits the env var by
# whitespace and appends to @ARGV.  Documents the
# **env-var-as-extra-argv pattern** in Perl — second
# documented occurrence (R269 shards had this for
# `SHARDS_OPTS` in Crystal).  CONVERGENT design
# pattern across Crystal + Perl — confirming this is
# a common cross-language Unix-tool idiom.
#
# Critical extraction note: cpanm uses **stdin pipe-
# detection** at Compat.pm:231 — `if (!@ARGV && $0
# ne '-' && !-t STDIN) { push @ARGV, $self->
# load_argv_from_fh(\*STDIN); }` reads module names
# from STDIN if no args provided AND stdin is piped
# (not a TTY).  Documents the **stdin pipe-mode
# detection** pattern in Perl — 4TH language now
# (Rust irust R273, Rust koto R274, Dart gpth R279,
# Perl cpanm R281).  Pattern documented in **4 corpus
# rounds across 3 languages** — extremely strong
# evidence for the universal Unix-tool idiom.  Perl
# uses `-t STDIN` test (file-test operator that
# returns true for TTY).
#
# Critical extraction note: cpanm uses **sub { ... }
# callback handlers** at Compat.pm:157, 159, 164,
# 165, 166, 170, 171, 180, 181, 191, 193-197, 207,
# 219, 221-225 — ~25 callback handlers.  Used for:
# (a) updating multiple fields when a single flag is
# given, (b) computing default values via method
# calls (e.g. `$self->maybe_abs($_[1])`), (c) setting
# command dispatch (e.g. `'i|install' => sub {
# $self->{cmd} = 'install' }`).  Documents the
# **subroutine callback for complex flag handling**
# in Perl — distinct from simple scalar-reference
# binding (`\$self->{flag}`) which Getopt::Long
# auto-handles.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
  '(-V --version)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
  '(-f --force)'{-f,--force}'[force install, install even when tests fail]' \
  '(-n --notest --no-notest)'{-n,--notest}'[do NOT run tests after install]' \
  '(-n --notest --no-notest)--no-notest[run tests (default; auto-negatable via ! suffix)]' \
  '--test-only[run tests but do not install]' \
  '(-S --sudo --no-sudo)'{-S,--sudo}'[use sudo for installation]' \
  '(-S --sudo --no-sudo)--no-sudo[do NOT use sudo]' \
  '(-v --verbose)'{-v,--verbose}'[verbose output]' \
  '(-q --quiet --no-quiet)'{-q,--quiet}'[quiet mode]' \
  '(-q --quiet --no-quiet)--no-quiet[not quiet]' \
  '(--verify --no-verify)--verify[verify signatures of distros]' \
  '(--verify --no-verify)--no-verify[do NOT verify signatures]' \
  '--perl=[install modules with the specified Perl]:perl:_files' \
  '(-l --local-lib)'{-l+,--local-lib=}'[specify local::lib compatible directory for install]:dir:_files -/' \
  '(-L --local-lib-contained)'{-L+,--local-lib-contained=}'[self-contained local::lib install dir]:dir:_files -/' \
  '(--self-contained --no-self-contained)--self-contained[install all non-core modules locally]' \
  '(--self-contained --no-self-contained)--no-self-contained[do NOT bundle non-core deps]' \
  '*--mirror=[mirror URL (repeatable; =s@ suffix)]:url:' \
  '--mirror-only[only use mirrors; skip CPAN.org]' \
  '--mirror-index=[mirror index file]:file:_files' \
  '(-M --from)'{-M+,--from=}'[shortcut for --mirror URL --mirror-only]:url:' \
  '--cpanmetadb=[URL of MetaDB server (cpanmetadb.plackperl.org by default)]:url:' \
  '(--cascade-search --no-cascade-search)--cascade-search[search mirrors in order until found]' \
  '(--cascade-search --no-cascade-search)--no-cascade-search[do NOT cascade-search]' \
  '(--prompt --no-prompt)--prompt[do interactive prompts on dependency conflicts]' \
  '(--prompt --no-prompt)--no-prompt[disable interactive prompts]' \
  '--installdeps[install dependencies for the current module]' \
  '(--skip-installed --no-skip-installed)--skip-installed[skip already-installed modules (default)]' \
  '(--skip-installed --no-skip-installed)--no-skip-installed[do NOT skip already-installed]' \
  '(--skip-satisfied --no-skip-satisfied)--skip-satisfied[skip if version requirement already satisfied]' \
  '(--skip-satisfied --no-skip-satisfied)--no-skip-satisfied[do NOT skip satisfied]' \
  '--reinstall[reinstall even if module already installed]' \
  '(--interactive --no-interactive)--interactive[ask before installing each module]' \
  '(--interactive --no-interactive)--no-interactive[non-interactive (default)]' \
  '(-i --install)'{-i,--install}'[install (default command)]' \
  '--info[print info about distribution and exit]' \
  '--look[shell-into the unpacked distribution; do not install]' \
  '(-U --uninstall)'{-U,--uninstall}'[uninstall module]' \
  '--self-upgrade[upgrade cpanm itself]' \
  '(--uninst-shadows --no-uninst-shadows)--uninst-shadows[uninstall shadow files of previous installations]' \
  '(--uninst-shadows --no-uninst-shadows)--no-uninst-shadows[do NOT uninstall shadows]' \
  '(--lwp --no-lwp)--lwp[use LWP::UserAgent for downloads]' \
  '(--lwp --no-lwp)--no-lwp[do NOT use LWP]' \
  '(--wget --no-wget)--wget[use wget for downloads]' \
  '(--wget --no-wget)--no-wget[do NOT use wget]' \
  '(--curl --no-curl)--curl[use curl for downloads]' \
  '(--curl --no-curl)--no-curl[do NOT use curl]' \
  '--auto-cleanup=[auto-cleanup .cpanm/work older than N days]:days:' \
  '(--man-pages --no-man-pages)--man-pages[install man pages (default true)]' \
  '(--man-pages --no-man-pages)--no-man-pages[do NOT install man pages]' \
  '--scandeps[scan and print dependencies; do not install]' \
  '--showdeps[show direct dependencies; do not install]' \
  '--format=[output format for --scandeps (tree/json/yaml/etc.)]:format:(tree json yaml dists))' \
  '--save-dists=[save downloaded distros to DIR]:dir:_files -/' \
  '(--skip-configure --no-skip-configure)--skip-configure[skip Makefile.PL/Build.PL configure step]' \
  '(--skip-configure --no-skip-configure)--no-skip-configure[run configure step]' \
  '(--static-install --no-static-install)--static-install[use static install for compatible distros]' \
  '(--static-install --no-static-install)--no-static-install[do NOT static-install]' \
  '(--dev --no-dev)--dev[install development releases]' \
  '(--dev --no-dev)--no-dev[do NOT install development releases]' \
  '(--metacpan --no-metacpan)--metacpan[use MetaCPAN API for module info]' \
  '(--metacpan --no-metacpan)--no-metacpan[do NOT use MetaCPAN]' \
  '(--report-perl-version --no-report-perl-version)--report-perl-version[report Perl version with HTTP requests]' \
  '(--report-perl-version --no-report-perl-version)--no-report-perl-version[do NOT report Perl version]' \
  '--configure-timeout=[configure step timeout in seconds (=i integer)]:seconds:' \
  '--build-timeout=[build step timeout in seconds (=i integer)]:seconds:' \
  '--test-timeout=[test step timeout in seconds (=i integer)]:seconds:' \
  '(--with-develop --without-develop)--with-develop[install develop dependencies]' \
  '(--with-develop --without-develop)--without-develop[do NOT install develop dependencies]' \
  '(--with-configure --without-configure)--with-configure[install configure dependencies]' \
  '(--with-configure --without-configure)--without-configure[do NOT install configure dependencies]' \
  '*--with-feature=[install optional feature (repeatable)]:feature:' \
  '*--without-feature=[disable optional feature (repeatable)]:feature:' \
  '--with-all-features[install all optional features]' \
  '(--pp --pureperl --no-pureperl)'{--pp,--pureperl}'[force pure-Perl install where possible]' \
  '(--pp --pureperl --no-pureperl)--no-pureperl[allow XS modules]' \
  '--cpanfile=[path to cpanfile (=s string)]:file:_files -g "cpanfile"' \
  '*:module name (Module::Name) or distribution URL/path:'
